author: rjung
msg: Fix link path for bundled expat used by apr-util.
Linking was broken after moving libexpat from
xml/expat/lib to xml/expat, which is the default
location for the original expat library.
The breakage only occured when using bundled expat
without explicitely giving "--with-expat=builtin" on
BeOS, Darwin, AIX and CYGWIN. Those platforms
link explicitely against libexpat. The other *nix
platforms just leave the expat symbols unresolved
and the app using apr-util needs to load libexpat
during runtime linking.

author: mamta
msg: DERBY-4835 Trigger plan does not recompile with upgrade from 10.5.3.0 to 10.6.1.0 causing java.lang.NoSuchMethodError

The problem was that the clearing of stored statements during the upgrade was conditional. The clearing should happen unconditionally during upgrade. Unconditional clearing of SPSes has fixed the problem with this jira.
Also, added a test in upgrade suite for triggers. The test has been added to BasicSetup.java which will ensure that this trigger test will automatically get run with even future releases.
